# This repo-root file exists only as a landing point for tooling that
# scans for `.env.example` at the repository root.
#
# The web application (apps/web) is a separate npm workspace and Vite
# build root, so its VITE_-prefixed environment variables must live in
# apps/web/.env.local (git-ignored), not here. Copy the real template:
#
#   cp apps/web/.env.example apps/web/.env.local
#
# See apps/web/.env.example for the full list of keys (VITE_API_BASE_URL,
# VITE_FIREBASE_*, VITE_APP_*) and what each one controls.
